{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease a round ovenproof dish (approx. 18 x 6 cm) and set aside.","Place cheddar cheese, mozzarella and Parmesan cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>4 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place water and 2 pinches sea salt, to taste into mixing bowl and heat <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add pasta to mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position and weigh broccoli into it. Steam <b>8-10 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>. Transfer pasta and broccoli into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven grill to 200°C.","Place butter, plain flour, milk, ground nutmeg, mustard powder, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and cook <b>6 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add 70 g of the reserved grated cheese and heat <b>1 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add reserved pasta and broccoli and combine <b>15 sec\/\/speed 1<b>.","Transfer into prepared dish then top with remaining grated cheese and paprika. Place under grill (200°C) for 5 minutes or until cheese is golden. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["oil, for greasing","30 g cheddar cheese, cut into cubes (3 cm)","30 g mozzarella cheese, cut into cubes (3 cm)","30 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into cubes (3 cm)","1200 g water","½ - 1 tsp sea salt, to taste, plus 2 pinches extra for cooking water","80 g macaroni pasta","150 g broccoli, cut into small florets","10 g butter","1 tbsp plain flour","100 g milk","1 pinch ground nutmeg","½ tsp mustard powder","½ - 1 tsp ground black pepper, to taste","1 pinch sweet paprika"]}],"id":"r71939","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-iWQscNmz-Oo\/XZWZ8Zdyy3I\/AAAAAAAAeT0\/TW-OPH1TFXgya4jB4AozcW8IxQf1hgigACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_pb6my3VaQbZnltDz.png","title":"Broccoli and three cheese pasta bake","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"23.7 g","fat":"21 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36 g","calories":"1851 kJ \/ 441 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round ovenproof dish (18 x 6 cm), thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, oven grill","hintsAndTricks":["Broccoli has impressive health benefits and goes a long way to keeping you fighting fit, regardless of how busy your schedule. A 100 g serve of broccoli provides 150% of your RDI for calcium, is high in fibre; vitamin A; iron; vitamin K; B-complex vitamins; zinc; phosphorus and; phyto-nutrients.","Serve either as a main meal or as a side dish with grilled chicken or steak.","If making this dish for one, transfer any leftovers into a freezable container and place into the freezer to enjoy later in the week."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","2 portions"]}